0CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20arrives%20at%20the%20Allen%20%26amp%3B%20Company%20Sun%20Valley%20Conference%20on%20July%209%2C%202024%20in%20Sun%20Valley%2C%20Idaho.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668e1e5f39de72f47bc9e26e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223483%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20is%20quite%20the%20cool%20guy%20among%20students%20using%20his%20ChatGPT%20for%20help%20with%20their%20homework.%3Cp%3EKevork%20Djansezian%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20promises%20to%20change%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20but%20so%20far%2C%20it's%20being%20used%20a%20lot%20for%20homework%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20has%20a%20tool%20to%20detect%20if%20something%20was%20written%20by%20ChatGPT%20but%20hasn't%20released%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESam%20Altman%2C%20hero%20of%20the%20common%20student%2C%20scourge%20of%20the%20AP%20History%20teacher.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20came%20out%20in%20late%202022%2C%20it%20was%20instantly%20clear%20there%20was%20one%20immediate%20and%20obvious%20use%3A%20writing%20term%20papers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteachers-colleges-ways-chatgpt-proof-assignments-essays-prevent-cheating-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethorn%20in%20the%20side%20of%20teachers%20and%20professors%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20as%20generative%20AI%20is%20more%20widely%20adopted%2C%20has%20it%20become%20more%20than%20just%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-in-five-teens-chatgpt-say-used-it-for-schoolwork-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomework%20helper%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20new%20pieces%20of%20information%20point%20us%20toward%20a%20conclusion%20we%20probably%20all%20knew%20in%20our%20hearts%3A%20Chatbots%20and%20generative%20AI%20are%20a%20bonanza%20for%20students%20looking%20for%20writing%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%20just%20published%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2024%2F08%2F04%2Fchatgpt-use-real-ai-chatbot-conversations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhat%20do%20people%20really%20use%20chatbots%20for%3F%20It's%20a%20lot%20of%20sex%20and%20homework%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20They%20looked%20at%20a%20large%20research%20dataset%20of%20AI%20chatbot%20conversations%20called%20WildChat%20and%20categorized%20the%20conversations.%20They%20found%20that%20the%20most%20common%20use%20%E2%80%94%20at%2021%25%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0was%20%26quot%3Bcreative%20writing%20and%20role%20play.%26quot%3B%20A%20sample%20of%20what%20that%20might%20be%3A%20asking%20the%20bot%20to%20write%20fan%20fiction%2C%20movie%20scripts%2C%20or%20Dungeons%20%26amp%3B%20Dragons%20characters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20most%20common%20category%20of%20chatbot%20conversations%20%E2%80%94%20at%2018%25%20%E2%80%94%20was%20for%20homework%20help.%20(One%20example%3A%20%26quot%3BExplain%20the%20Monroe%20Doctrine%20in%20a%20sentence.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20lesser-used%20categories%20included%20things%20like%20search%2C%20translation%2C%20and%20coding%2Fprogramming%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20the%20Post's%20reporting%2C%20there's%20another%20new%20reason%20to%20suspect%20that%20homework%20%26quot%3Bhelp%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20maybe%20cheating!%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20massively%20popular%20use%20for%20ChatGPT%20and%20other%20text-based%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fai%2Fopenai-tool-chatgpt-cheating-writing-135b755a%3Fst%3Dk1xphc7ileyz7a4%26reflink%3Darticle_gmail_share%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20that%20OpenAI%20has%20been%20developing%20a%20tool%20that%20could%20detect%20writing%20that%20used%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20won't%20release%20the%20tool%20(yet).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tool%20would%20make%20it%20so%20that%20ChatGPT%20would%20create%20a%20sort%20of%20%26quot%3Bwatermark%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20way%20it%20chooses%20words.%20The%20watermark%20would%20be%20undetectable%20to%20human%20eyes%20but%20could%20be%20picked%20up%20by%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20would%20be%2099.9%25%20accurate%20in%20being%20able%20to%20tell%20if%20something%20was%20written%20by%20ChatGPT%20or%20a%20real%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20OpenAI%20hasn't%20released%20this%20tool%2C%20much%20to%20some%20people's%20frustration%20inside%20the%20company%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20OpenAI%20told%20the%20WSJ%20that%20the%20company%20had%20concerns%20the%20tool%20could%20hurt%20non-native%20English%20speakers%20who%20use%20ChatGPT.%20%26quot%3BThe%20text%20watermarking%20method%20we're%20developing%20is%20technically%20promising%20but%20has%20important%20risks%20we're%20weighing%20while%20we%20research%20alternatives%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20told%20the%20WSJ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOK%2C%20reasonable.%20I%20think%20we%20all%20like%20the%20idea%20of%20OpenAI%20taking%20its%20time%20and%20thinking%20long%20and%20hard%20about%20the%20potential%20harms%20of%20releasing%20a%20new%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here's%20the%20other%20part%3A%20According%20to%20the%20report%2C%20%26quot%3BOpenAI%20surveyed%20ChatGPT%20users%20and%20found%2069%25%20believe%20cheating%20detection%20technology%20would%20lead%20to%20false%20accusations%20of%20using%20AI.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ENearly%2030%25%20said%20they%20would%20use%20ChatGPT%20less%20if%20it%20deployed%20watermarks%20and%20a%20rival%20didn't.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3B%20(Emphasis%20mine).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20sounds%20like%20a%20pretty%20good%20sign%20that%20%26quot%3Bcheating%20on%20my%20homework%26quot%3B%